#: ../../T/the-X-that-can-be-Y-is-not-the-true-X.rst:5
msgid "the X that can be Y is not the true X"
msgstr "the X that can be Y is not the true X"

#: ../../T/the-X-that-can-be-Y-is-not-the-true-X.rst:7
msgid ""
"Yet another instance of hackerdom's peculiar attraction to mystical "
"references — a common humorous way of making exclusive statements about a "
"class of things. The template is from the *Tao te Ching*\\: \"The Tao which "
"can be spoken of is not the true Tao.\" The implication is often that the X "
"is a mystery accessible only to the enlightened. See the :ref:`trampoline` "
"entry for an example, and compare :ref:`has-the-X-nature`\\."
msgstr ""
"神秘的な言及へのハッカー界の奇妙な傾倒のさらにもう一つの例——あるクラスのものについて排他的な言明をする、よくあるユーモラスな方法。ひな型は\\ "
"*老子道徳経*\\ より:「語りうる道は真の道にあらず」。含意はしばしば、Xが悟りを開いた者だけがアクセスできる神秘であるというものだ。例については\\"
" :ref:`trampoline`\\ の項目を参照し、\\ :ref:`has-the-X-nature`\\ と比較せよ。"
